claim.claim-text:
1. An extraction column, comprising
a column having a wall, wherein the wall has a substantially circular perimeter;
a continuous porous coating disposed on the inner face of the wall, wherein the coating is made from the steps:
obtaining a first sol-gel precursor, wherein the first precursor is hydroxy-terminated poly(dimethylsiloxane), bis[(3-methyldimethoxysilyl)-propyl]polypropylene oxide, poly(tetrahydrofuran) 250, poly(ethylene glycol) MW 600, poly(dimethylsiloxane-co-diphenylsiloxane), dihydroxyterminated, or a derivative thereof;
adding an ionic liquid to the first sol-gel precursor to form a precursor-ionic liquid mixture, wherein the ionic liquid is a phosphonium-based ionic liquid, imidazolium-based ionic liquid, pyridinium-based ionic liquid, or a combination thereof;
mixing a second sol-gel precursor into the precursor-ionic liquid mixture, wherein the second sol-gel precursor is an alkoxy compound of an element M, where M is silicon, titanium, zirconium, germanium, vanadium, zinc, tantalum, niobium, tungsten; and
mixing a catalyst into the precursor-ionic liquid mixture to form a sol-gel mixture, wherein the catalyst is an acid, base, or fluoride compound.

8. The extraction column of claim 1, wherein the coating is made from the additional step of conditioning the extraction column, comprising the steps of
placing the extraction column in a gas chromatograph oven;
passing helium gas along the exterior surface of the coating;
elevating the temperature of the gas chromatograph oven at until the oven reaches a conditioning temperature;
where the conditioning temperature is 400° C. or below.
